TY  - JOUR
T1  - Dissection Methods for Solutions in Chance Constrained Programming Problems Under Discrete Distributions
AU  - Raike, William M.
Y1  - 1970/07/01
PY  - 1970
DA  - 1970/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.16.11.708
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.16.11.708
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 708
EP  - 715
VL  - 16
IS  - 11
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Under the assumption of discrete distributions for the random variables involved, deterministic equivalent problems are derived for a general class of chance constrained (but not necessarily linear) programming problems. These permit the explicit solution of such problems for all or most types of optimal stochastic decision rules which are of interest, including optimal multistage rules and not restricted to the class of linear rules. The formulation given encompasses certain cases of stochastic programming with recourse, and the deterministic equivalents derived for these reduce to well-known versions available in the literature.
AB  - Under the assumption of discrete distributions for the random variables involved, deterministic equivalent problems are derived for a general class of chance constrained (but not necessarily linear) programming problems. These permit the explicit solution of such problems for all or most types of optimal stochastic decision rules which are of interest, including optimal multistage rules and not restricted to the class of linear rules. The formulation given encompasses certain cases of stochastic programming with recourse, and the deterministic equivalents derived for these reduce to well-known versions available in the literature.
