TY  - JOUR
T1  - Price-Production Decisions with Deterministic Demand
AU  - Thomas, Joseph
Y1  - 1970/07/01
PY  - 1970
DA  - 1970/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.16.11.747
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.16.11.747
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 747
EP  - 750
VL  - 16
IS  - 11
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The problem of simultaneously making price and production decisions for a single product with a known deterministic demand function is considered. The objective is to maximize profit, and backorders are not allowed. Results which reduce the computations necessary for the pricing decision are given, and planning horizons are identified as in previous inventory research. These results are combined into an efficient forward algorithm.
AB  - The problem of simultaneously making price and production decisions for a single product with a known deterministic demand function is considered. The objective is to maximize profit, and backorders are not allowed. Results which reduce the computations necessary for the pricing decision are given, and planning horizons are identified as in previous inventory research. These results are combined into an efficient forward algorithm.
